{
  "stem": "443.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after the four day, I decided-- I pulled in a dead person.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Instead to go away, I laid down between the dead people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I stayed there two and a half days between the dead people.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the last two and a half days before we were liberated by the English.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's how I survived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "If I wouldn't have done this, probably, two days later, they would have pulled me into that-- that pile of-- of dead people.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was the only way I really survived.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was so weak, when the English came in, they kept on searching for live people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they heard me screaming, hollering, you know, call for help.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's how they took me away, in an ambulance.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they took me to a city where there was some hospitals.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was in that hospital for six weeks.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was a hospital with nuns, sisters.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] And I was treated just like a little baby.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They washed me and bathed me, put me in a clean bed, turned me over, put me over to the other side.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because you were so weak, you couldn't even turn over from one side to another.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They fed me, spoon fed, because there was nothing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Everything was dried up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was a lucky thing that I didn't eat anything in the camps, because unfortunately, when the English gave food in the camps, they give condensed milk and the-- the-- the ham that's rolled on papers in those-- in those pushkas, in those-- those cans.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And whoever ate that stuff just died.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The following day, whoever drank or ate did not come out alive.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
